    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like there's no point in \"healing\" or \"processing\" it. the house is just a tomb now. every little thing i do, like making coffee or cleaning up, it all feels so incredibly pointless. like i'm just wasting time in a life that doesn't even matter anymore. i'm just so exhausted from carrying this.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The pain of loss can be so all-consuming that it's hard to find meaning in even the simplest daily tasks. It's understandable that you feel like the world has changed and that nothing has the same value anymore. Allow yourself to acknowledge these feelings, and remember that it's okay to not be okay. You don't have to find a way to \"keep going\" just yet; simply taking one small step at a time can be a powerful first step towards navigating this new reality.",
      "source": "target",
